subSubSection.paragraph: Habitus Fig. 2 . Length +/- 650 µ. Colour dark brown. Antennae length +/- 238 µ. Distance across eyes 214 µ min, 228 µ max, 221 µ mean. Pronotum length 174 µ min, 188 µ max, 181 µ mean; width 324 µ min, 332 µ max, 328 µ mean; ratio width/length 1.76 . Detached elytron length 411 µ min, 437 µ max, 426 µ mean; width 211 µ min, 224 µ max, 219 µ mean; ratio length/width 1.94 , Fig. 21 . Ratio mean elytra length/mean pronotum length 2.35 . Skeletal details Figs. 10, 13 .
Etymology . From the Latin secubitus meaning lying or sleeping alone and referring to the absence of males.
Diagnosis . The form of the spermatheca which will quickly distinguish this species from all others.
